        // 1. Take 1 coin: N becomes N-1 (odd).
        //    Chanek gets 1 coin. The opponent faces N-1 coins.
        //    From N-1 coins, the opponent will get (N-1+1)/2 = N/2 coins.
        //    Chanek will get (N-1)/2 coins.
        //    So Chanek's total: 1 + (N-1)/2.
        // 2. Take N/2 coins: N becomes N/2 (can be even or odd).
        //    Chanek gets N/2 coins. The opponent faces N/2 coins.
        //    Let's analyze the N/2 part.
        //    If N/2 is odd, the opponent will take (N/2+1)/2 coins.
        //    Chanek will get (N/2-1)/2 coins.
        //    So Chanek's total: N/2 + (N/2-1)/2.
        //    If N/2 is even, the opponent will take N/4 coins.
        //    Chanek will get N/4 coins.
        //    So Chanek's total: N/2 + N/4.
