    // `(x & (val1 ^ val0)) ^ val0`

    // For `x=0`: `(0 & (val1 ^ val0)) ^ val0 = 0 ^ val0 = val0`. Correct.
    // For `x=1023`: `(1023 & (val1 ^ val0)) ^ val0`.
    // Since `val1 ^ val0` is a 10-bit number, `1023 & (val1 ^ val0)` is just `(val1 ^ val0)`.
    // So, `(val1 ^ val0) ^ val0 = val1`. Correct.

    // This sequence uses at most 2 operations: `&` and `^`.
